    ‚àá {r}‚Üê_Register(method path rarg);handler;options;norm;existing
      :Access Private Instance
      :If 1‚âÝ‚â°rarg                           ‚çù nested: ('HandlerName' options)
          (handler options)‚Üêrarg
      :ElseIf ‚çï‚çõ‚â°rarg
          handler‚Üêrarg                     ‚çù simple string
          options‚Üê()
      :Else
        ‚éïSIGNAL ‚äÇ('EN' 11)('Message' ('STARK: Right argument to Register must be a string (handler name) or a 2-element vector (handler name, options)'))
      :EndIf
      ‚çù Check for duplicate routes: normalize {param} segments so {id} and {user_id} match
      norm‚Üê_NormalizePath path
      :If 0<‚â¢_routes
          existing‚Üê((‚éïC¬®_routes.method)‚àä‚äÇ‚éïC method)/_routes
          :If 0<‚â¢existing
              :If (‚äÇnorm)‚àä_NormalizePath¬®existing.pattern
                  ‚éïSIGNAL ‚äÇ('EN' 11)('Message' ('STARK: Duplicate route: ',method,' ',path,' conflicts with an existing registration'))
              :EndIf
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
      r‚Üê(
        method: method
        pattern: ,path
        handler: handler
        options: options
      )
      _routes,‚Üêr
    ‚àá

    ‚çù Cover function for 7162‚å∂ (mangle string into valid APL name)
    _Mangle‚Üê{0(7162‚å∂)‚çµ}

    ‚çù Replace {param} segments with a placeholder so structurally identical paths match
    _NormalizePath‚Üê{‚çµ/‚ç®~+\‚àä+/¬Ø1 0‚åΩ¬®1 ¬Ø1√ó‚Üì'{}'‚àò.=‚çµ}

    ‚àá r‚Üê{value}DebugLevel level
    ‚çù monadic: return 1 if level is within Debug (powers of 2)
    ‚çù dyadic:  return value unless level is within Debug
      r‚Üê‚à®/((7‚ç¥2)‚ä§‚äÉDebug)‚à®.‚àß(7‚ç¥2)‚ä§level
      :If 0‚âÝ‚éïNC'value'
          r‚Üêvalue/‚ç®~r
      :EndIf
    ‚àá

    stopIf‚Üê{1‚àä‚çµ:-‚éïTRAP‚Üê0 'C' '‚éï‚Üê''Stopped for debugging... (Press Ctrl-Enter)''' ‚ãÑ shy‚Üê0}

    ‚çù pattern pathMatch path ‚Üí (matched pathParams)
    pathMatch‚Üê{
        patSplit pathSplit‚Üê'/'(‚âÝ‚äÜ‚ä¢)¬®‚ç∫ ‚çµ
        pathSplit‚â¢‚ç•‚â¢patSplit:0()
        varMask‚Üê'{'=‚äÉ¬®patSplit
        ‚â¢/(‚äÇ~varMask)/¬®patSplit pathSplit:0()
        names‚Üê({1‚Üì¬Ø1‚Üì‚çµ}¬®patSplit[‚ç∏varMask])
        1(()‚éïVSET‚Üì‚çâ‚Üënames(pathSplit[‚ç∏varMask]))
    }

    ‚çù Route an incoming Jarvis request to the matching handler
    ‚àá result‚Üê_Dispatch req;routes;r;matched;pp
      :Access Public Instance
      stopIf DebugLevel 64                          ‚çù stop before routing
      routes‚Üê((‚éïC¬®_routes.method)‚àä‚äÇ‚éïC req.Method)/_routes
      :For r :In routes
          (matched pp)‚Üêr.pattern pathMatch req.Endpoint
          :If matched
              req.PathParams‚Üêpp
              req.QueryParams‚Üê(‚éïNS '')‚éïVSET{(,‚äÉ‚çµ)(2‚äÉ‚çµ)}¬®‚Üìreq.QueryParams
              :If '_'=‚äÉr.handler
                  result‚Üê(‚çér.handler)req          ‚çù internal handler (on Stark)
              :Else
                  :If DebugLevel 32
                      ‚éï‚Üê'STARK: ',req.Method,' ',req.Endpoint,' ‚Üí ',r.handler
                  :EndIf
                  stopIf DebugLevel 2              ‚çù stop before user handler
                  :Trap 0 DebugLevel 1             ‚çù disable trap if bit 1 set (stop on error)
                      result‚Üê(Handlers‚çér.handler)req
                  :Else
                      ‚éïSIGNAL‚äÇ‚éïDMX               ‚çù re-signal to let Jarvis return 500
                  :EndTrap
              :EndIf
              :Return
          :EndIf
      :EndFor
      req.Fail 404
      result‚Üê(
        detail: 'Not Found'
      )
